27 reach a collective bargaining agreement within 120 days after beginning negotiations or on or
28 before February 1 of an odd-numbered year, whichever is earlier, unless the parties agree to a
29 later date. (NRS 288.570) Section 2 of this bill authorizes parties who do not reach an
30 agreement to request a mediator: (1) after at least six meetings of negotiations or on or before
31 September 5 of an even-numbered year when one of the parties is a bargaining unit with an
32 existing collective bargaining agreement; or (2) after at least eight meetings of negotiations or
33 90 days after the parties begin negotiating, whichever is earlier, when one of the parties is a
34 bargaining unit negotiating to enter a collective bargaining agreement for the first time.
35 Under existing law, if the representative of the Executive Department and the exclusive
36 representative of a bargaining unit do not reach a collective bargaining agreement through
37 mediation within 10 days after the appointment of a mediator, mediation is required to cease
38 and the parties are required to begin arbitration proceedings on or before February 15 unless
39 the parties agree to a later date. The arbitrator is then required to render a decision on or
40 before March 5. (NRS 288.575) Section 3 of this bill: (1) requires arbitration proceedings to
41 begin on or before September 15, rather than February 15; and (2) requires the arbitrator to
42 render a decision on or before December 5, rather than March 5. Section 3 also eliminates the
43 authority for the parties to agree to a later deadline for the decision of the arbitrator.
44 Under existing law, the Economic Forum, a panel of appointed economic and financial
45 experts, prepares a written report of its projections of economic indicators and an estimate of
46 future state revenue for the Governor and Legislature on or before December 3 of each even-
47 numbered year. (NRS 353.228) Section 4 of this bill requires that such a report instead be
48 prepared by November 15 of each even-numbered year.
49 Section 4.3 of this bill makes an appropriation to the Division of Human Resource
50 Management of the Department of Administration for certain personnel, travel,
51 operating and information services costs.
52 Section 4.7 of this bill makes an appropriation to the Office of the Governor for
53 certain personnel, operating, equipment and information services costs.
